@page "/privacy"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@layout PublicLayout

<!-- Page Title: Privacy Policy - FDX.trading -->

<section class="py-5 bg-white">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-8">
                <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="text-muted mb-4">Last updated: January 15, 2025</p>

                <div class="prose">
                    <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
                    <p>FDX Trading Ltd. ("we", "our", "us") collects information to provide and improve our food sourcing and trade platform.</p>
                    
                    <h5>Information you provide:</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Account information (name, email, company, phone)</li>
                        <li>Business information (products, certifications, trade data)</li>
                        <li>Communication data (messages, documents, support requests)</li>
                        <li>Payment information (processed securely via third parties)</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>Information collected automatically:</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Usage data (features used, time spent, interactions)</li>
                        <li>Device information (IP address, browser type, operating system)</li>
                        <li>Cookies and similar technologies (see Cookie Policy)</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="mt-5">2. How We Use Information</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Provide and maintain the FDX platform</li>
                        <li>Match buyers with appropriate suppliers</li>
                        <li>Verify compliance and certifications</li>
                        <li>Process transactions and payments</li>
                        <li>Send notifications about orders and shipments</li>
                        <li>Improve our services and develop new features</li>
                        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="mt-5">3. Information Sharing</h3>
                    <p>We share information only as necessary:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>With your consent:</strong> When you authorize specific sharing</li>
                        <li><strong>Business partners:</strong> Suppliers, buyers, and experts involved in your transactions</li>
                        <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> Azure, payment processors, email services</li>
                        <li><strong>Legal requirements:</strong> When required by law or to protect rights</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="mt-5">4. Data Security</h3>
                    <p>We implement industry-standard security measures:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Encryption in transit and at rest</li>
                        <li>Azure AD / Entra ID authentication</li>
                        <li>Regular security audits and monitoring</li>
                        <li>Access controls and audit logging</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="mt-5">5. Your Rights (GDPR/CCPA)</h3>
                    <p>You have the right to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Access your personal data</li>
                        <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
                        <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
                        <li>Export your data (data portability)</li>
                        <li>Object to certain processing</li>
                        <li>Withdraw consent</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="mt-5">6. Data Retention</h3>
                    <p>We retain data as long as necessary for business purposes and legal requirements:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Active account data: Duration of account plus 30 days</li>
                        <li>Transaction records: 7 years for tax/legal compliance</li>
                        <li>Marketing data: Until opt-out or 2 years of inactivity</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="mt-5">7. International Transfers</h3>
                    <p>Data may be transferred to and processed in:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Microsoft Azure data centers (EU, US, Israel regions)</li>
                        <li>Countries where our service providers operate</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>We ensure appropriate safeguards via Standard Contractual Clauses.</p>

                    <h3 class="mt-5">8. Children's Privacy</h3>
                    <p>FDX is not intended for users under 18. We do not knowingly collect data from minors.</p>

                    <h3 class="mt-5">9. Updates to This Policy</h3>
                    <p>We may update this policy and will notify you of material changes via email or platform notification.</p>

                    <h3 class="mt-5">10. Contact Us</h3>
                    <p>For privacy questions or to exercise your rights:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Email: privacy@foodz-x.com</li>
                        <li>Data Protection Officer: dpo@foodz-x.com</li>
                        <li>Address: FDX Trading Ltd., Tel Aviv, Israel</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-5 p-4 bg-light rounded">
                    <h5>Cookie Settings</h5>
                    <p>Manage your cookie preferences <a href="/cookies">here</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>